<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-02-10"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 10, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 4th instant, relative to the circumstances
                            under which the United States ship <pb facs="0551" n="509" xml:id="pg_509"/> Tuscarora recently exercised the belligerent right
                            of visit, in the case of the British merchant vessel Thistle, and to
                            inform you that a copy of it has been communicated to the Secretary of
                            the Navy.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, your lordship’s obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>